# Skillet Project Rules

Read `.docs/OVERVIEW.md` before structural or behavioral changes.

## Target Platform

- WotLK **3.3.5a** only (`Interface: 30300` in `Skillet-Enhanced.toc`)
- Use legacy tradeskill APIs: `GetTradeSkill*`, `DoTradeSkill`, `SetTradeSkillItem`, `GetMerchantItem*`
- Never introduce Retail APIs (`C_TradeSkillUI`, etc.)

## Preserve Existing Behavior

- Skillet replaces Blizzard's tradeskill UI via `TRADE_SKILL_*` events; do not break that interception path
- Honor guard conditions: skip linked tradeskills (`IsTradeSkillLinked()`), unknown professions, EnchantingSell conflict
- Queue persistence, shopping list aggregation, alt inventory, and vendor auto-buy are core features — regression-test mentally when touching related code
- Debounced handlers are intentional: bag rescan (250 ms), skill-line cleanup (10 s). Do not remove debouncing without replacement

## Change Scope

- Minimize diff size; fix the reported issue only
- Do **not** edit vendored code under `Libs/` unless explicitly requested
- Do **not** refactor Ace2 patterns to modern Ace3/LibStub-only architecture
- Do **not** call `:SetScale()` on frames (removed in v1.5; crashes Mac client)
- Update `Skillet-Enhanced.toc` load order only when adding/removing addon-authored files

## Module Ownership

| Area | Files |
|------|-------|
| Lifecycle & events | `Skillet.lua` |
| Recipe cache & craft queue | `SkilletStitch-1.1.lua` |
| Queue persistence | `SkilletQueue.lua` |
| Data accessors | `TradeskillInfo.lua` |
| Public mod API | `ThirdPartyHooks.lua` |
| SavedVariables migration | `Upgrades.lua` |
| Alt inventory bridge | `LibPossessions.lua` |
| UI | `UI/*.lua`, `UI/*.xml` |
| Strings | `Locale/Locale-*.lua` |

Put new logic in the owning module; avoid cross-cutting edits.

## File Header

New addon-authored `.lua` files must retain the GPL v3+ copyright block used in existing files.
